569	// EvidenceReviewExcludePathspecs returns git pathspec-exclusion fragments
570	// applied when review-prompt synthesis runs `git show <rev>` over the
571	// evidence commit. Broader than EvidenceLandExcludePathspecs: excludes
572	// prompt.md and usage.json too, because even though they're tracked for
573	// audit, they're execution-artifact noise from the reviewer's
574	// perspective — the reviewer wants to see the implementation diff, not
575	// the prior attempt's prompt or token counters. This also protects
